Sec. 102.166. RECORDS. (a) Each person subject to a marketing
agreement or license shall:
(1) maintain records reflecting the person's operation
under the agreement or license;
(2) permit the department to inspect those records; and
(3) furnish to the department information requested by the
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

- 684 -

AGRICULTURE CODE

department relating to the person's operations under the agreement or
license.
(b) Except as otherwise provided by this subsection,
information obtained under this section is confidential and may not
be disclosed to any person. The information may be disclosed to a
person with a similar right to obtain the information or to an
attorney employed by an administrative committee to give legal advice
on the information. In addition, the information may be disclosed in
response to a court order.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1272, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

